title: Army Major sacked over security protocol breach
description: An Army Major in India has been dismissed by President Droupadi Murmu for breaching security protocols and compromising national security. The Major was found to have kept classified documents on his electronic devices and was in contact with a Pakistani intelligence operative through social media. The investigation also led to the discovery of a WhatsApp group with several military officers and spouses as members, who are now facing a separate probe. Some members of the group have received show cause notices for violating social media policies.

title: 2 coaches, engine of train derail in Prayagraj
description: Around 9 pm on Tuesday, two coaches and the locomotive of the Suhaildev Express, which operates between Anand Vihar in Delhi and Ghazipur, derailed at Prayagraj railway station. This incident happened just two days after a collision between passenger trains in Andhra Pradesh resulted in the tragic loss of 13 lives and injuries to 50 individuals. The derailment occurred on the railway track adjacent to platform No. 9, according to sources. No casualty was reported, North Central Railway's chief PRO Himanshu Shekhar Upadhyay said.

title: What is behind Delhi's poor AQI?
description: According to the Decision Support System (DSS), emissions from NCR districts such as Noida, Gurgaon, Faridabad, and Bulandshahr are major contributors to pollution in Delhi. The DSS estimates the daily contribution of pollution sources in Delhi's PM2.5 based on meteorological conditions. Noida was found to be the highest contributor to regional pollution in Delhi's PM2.5, followed by Ghaziabad and Bulandshahr. Industries and bio-fuel burning are also significant contributors to pollution.

title: 8 ft-tall gold-plated marble throne for Ram Lalla idol
description: The Ram temple in Ayodhya will have an eight-foot-tall gold-plated marble throne for Ram Lalla's idol. The throne, being made by artisans in Rajasthan, will reach Ayodhya by December 15. The temple construction work has been intensified, with the ground floor expected to be ready by the same date. Ram devotees have also donated gold and silver items which will be melted down for safekeeping. The first floor is 80% complete, and the construction of the sanctum sanctorum is finished. The work on other areas of the temple is also progressing.

title: Speeding caused 71% of all road deaths last year: Govt data
description: Speeding was responsible for 70 per cent of road deaths in India in 2022, which saw a record-breaking 168,491 fatalities and 440,000 injuries. Failure to use safety devices, such as helmets and seat belts, was the second leading cause of deaths. Over 50,000 two-wheeler riders died due to not wearing helmets, while 16,715 deaths were linked to not wearing seat belts. India has the highest number of road fatalities globally, accounting for 11% of total deaths.

title: Opposition claims tapping; Govt denies, asks Apple to join probe
description: Apple has clarified that the alerts sent to individuals in 150 countries about state-sponsored attackers targeting their iPhones may be "false alarms" and did not specifically refer to any state actor. The Indian government denied the charges of snooping and criticized the opposition for making baseless claims. The government has asked Apple to provide accurate information on the alleged attacks. Opposition politicians claimed to have received messages from Apple warning about potential targeting by state-sponsored attackers.

title: Maratha quota violence on, Net blocked in 2 districts
description: Internet services have been suspended in the Maharashtra districts of Jalna and Beed until November 2 due to ongoing violence and arson related to the Maratha community's demand for reservation. A Maratha youth was found hanging in his home in Ahmednagar district with a suicide note expressing frustration over the lack of reservation. Cases will be filed against those involved in violence and arson, and restrictions have been imposed on protests in certain districts. P

title: Keep details of electoral bond donations ready, SC tells EC
description: The Supreme Court has announced that it will examine the details of political party donations made through electoral bonds. The move could potentially cause trouble for parties that have benefited from such donations, as there are concerns of a quid pro quo relationship between the donors and the favored regimes. The court has requested that the Election Commission provide the details of electoral bond funding as per their previous interim order. The validity of anonymous funding through electoral bonds has been challenged by several petitions.

title: Cop shot in 3rd targeted attack in 3 days in J&K
description: An off-duty J&K police head constable, Ghulam Mohammed Dar, was shot and killed by terrorists near his home in Kashmir's Baramulla district. Dar, who leaves behind his wife and seven daughters, was taken to a hospital where he was pronounced dead. Security forces are conducting a manhunt for the terrorists. The increase in targeted attacks is believed to be linked to security operations against terrorist infiltration attempts from Pakistan before winter sets in.

title: Customs fails to detect passenger with 1kg gold concealed in rectum
Making reels with firearms lands Bihar youth in jail
description: In a video which has gone viral on social media, the youth, identified as Ayush Paswan, 20, could be seen riding a horse while displaying arms in right hand and holding a cigarette in another.

title: Security up on Shinde's home turf after violence
description: The police said that after the agitators torched the bungalows of MLAs in Marathwada as well as political party offices belonging to elected representatives, the Thane city police are on high alert being the home turf of the chief minister.

title: All you need to know about Pakistan's chances of reaching WC semis
description: Pakistan halted their four-match losing streak by securing a resounding seven-wicket triumph over Bangladesh, revitalising their slim chances of securing a spot in the World Cup semi-finals. Shaheen's remarkable bowling performance, claiming figures of 3-23, was instrumental in Pakistan's endeavor to restrict Bangladesh to a mere 204 runs in 45.1 overs at Kolkata's Eden Gardens. This win breathed new life into Pakistan's slim chances of making it to the semi-finals, as they now have six points from seven matches.

title: Swiss woman murder: Cops scan footage of 350 CCTVs
description: As per a statement from a police officer, these cameras encompass the ones positioned at locations where the accused, Gurpreet Singh, took Nina Berger before committing the crime, which involved her murder and the disposal of her body outside a school in the Tilak Nagar area in western Delhi.

title: World Cup: Pakistan knock Bangladesh out to keep semis hopes alive
description: Pakistan kept their hopes of reaching the semi-finals of the 50-overs World Cup alive after a dominant seven-wicket victory against Bangladesh at Eden Gardens in Kolkata on Tuesday. Bangladesh, opting to bat first, struggled to recover from an early top-order collapse and could only muster a modest total of 204 runs before being all out in the 46th over at the Eden Gardens. Pakistan's three-pronged pace attack made a strong impression, both with the new ball and during the death overs.

title: Don't miss these financial deadlines in November 2023
description: In November, there are several important financial deadlines and changes that you should be aware of. These include the submission deadline for the life certificate, as well as the last dates to invest in special fixed deposits.

title: 'Can’t run sweatshops': K'taka IT min on 70-hr work week idea
description: Priyank Kharge, Karnataka IT minister, has stated that companies cannot force individuals to work extra hours and should not run sweatshops. This comes in response to Infosys co-founder Narayana Murthy's suggestion that Indian youth should work 70 hours a week. Kharge believes that companies should focus on productivity rather than the number of hours worked. He also appreciates Murthy's contribution to the IT industry and acknowledges that there are differing opinions on the matter.

title: Easier visas for STEM students and skilled workers soon
description: The Biden administration intends to optimize the visa interview and review process to encourage highly skilled immigrants and nonimmigrants with expertise in critical areas to remain, study, and work in the United States.

title: Shaikh Dasthagiri, approver in Vivekananda murder, arrested
description: It is learned that the Muslim girl, who is closely related to Dasthagiri, had married a scheduled caste boy last month, much against the will of her family members.

title: How Rohit Sharma performed over the years at Wankhede
description: From the days of a babyfaced upcoming batter hailed by many for his talent, Rohit has come a long way as he will be captaining Team India in a World Cup match, a tournament he had missed out as a youngster back in 2011. The omission still pains India's 'Hitman' as he had to settle for watching Men in Blue lift the trophy after 28 years with a memorable win against Sri Lanka in the final at the same venue.  12 years later, he would be aiming to make his first World Cup match at Wankhede special for not only himself but his country too.

title: Police head constable shot dead by terrorists in J&K
Halloween: All you need to know about this spooky holiday
description: Halloween is a widely celebrated holiday with origins in ancient Celtic traditions. It has evolved over time and is now characterized by dressing up in costumes, carving pumpkins, and going trick-or-treating. The phrase "trick-or-treat" originated as a playful threat, with children promising to play tricks on homeowners if they didn't receive treats. It has since become a lighthearted way to merge the traditions of dressing up and receiving treats, while also promoting community interaction.

title: Photos: HP villages to get water from 15k feet height
description: The length of this irrigation project will be 5 km and 470 meters. Around Rs 9.32 crore will be spent on this project under NABARD. It is being claimed no other irrigation project at such an altitude exists at the moment in the country and this project will be a record in itself and would benefit 1264 people of the area.

title: Dust might have snuffed out the dinosaurs
description: A recent study published in Nature Geoscience has revealed that fine silicate dust played a significant role in the global cooling that occurred after the asteroid impact that led to the extinction of nonavian dinosaurs. The dust, which lingered in the atmosphere for up to 15 years, caused a long and dark winter, interrupting photosynthetic activity on Earth. The research provides valuable insights into the post-impact period and helps to understand the impact on the dinosaur population.

title: Jammu Police files chargesheet in female doctor's murder case
description: The case comes as a shocker for Jammuites after Shraddha Walker was allegedly killed by her live-in partner, Aftab Amin Poonawala, on May 18, 2022 in New Delhi and was cut into 35 pieces to dispose of the body.

title: Manipur police officer shot dead by militants in Moreh
description: A government statement said that the cabinet has noted that Kumar, a resident of Haobam Marak Chingtham Leikai in Imphal was killed in "unprovoked firing by armed Kuki militants."

title: Woman making terror threats, shouting Allahu Akbar shot in Paris
description: French police shot and seriously injured an unarmed woman wearing an Islamic veil after she threatened to blow herself up and screamed 'Allahu Akbar' at a metro station in Paris. The incident occurred after passengers on a train alerted the police, who managed to isolate the woman. Despite warnings, the woman did not respond, leading the police to open fire. The woman's condition is critical, and the incident has heightened fears in Paris, leading to increased security measures. This incident comes amidst a wave of bomb hoaxes and acts of violence in France.

title: Q2 GDP number will surprise everyone on the upside: RBI chief
Over 40% Canadians say there are too many immigrants: Survey
description: A recent survey conducted by Environics reveals that 44% of Canadians believe there is too much immigration in the country, reflecting growing economic concerns. This marks a significant increase from the previous year, with a reversal of the trend of public support for immigration. However, 74% still believe that immigration is good for Canada and its economy. The survey also highlights that inflation, cost of living are the main concerns for those surveyed.

title: Tendulkar's statue inside Wankhede to be inaugurated on Wednesday
description: A life-size statue honouring the cricket legend Sachin Tendulkar is set to be unveiled on Wednesday on the eve of the World Cup match between India and Sri Lanka in Mumbai. Pramod Kamble, a painter-sculptor from Ahmednagar in the state, is credited with creating the statue that will stand as a tribute to Tendulkar's legacy. Notably, this installation at the Wankhede Stadium comes almost a decade after Tendulkar's final game for India, which took place against the West Indies in a two-match Test series back in November 2013.

title: Why nearly Afghan nationals are being forced to flee Pak
description: Pakistan will begin cracking down on undocumented immigrants, including nearly 2 million Afghan nationals, starting Nov 1. The deportation will be carried out in phases, targeting those with criminal records first. The move is driven by rising militancy, an economic crisis, and strained relations between the Taliban government in Afghanistan and Pakistan. Pakistan hopes that the deportation will reduce unemployment but it is unlikely to have a positive impact on the country's inflation rate.

title: Quota stir: Fadnavis warns of action over violence
description: Speaking to the media immediately after the state cabinet meeting at Mantralaya, Fadnavis said some people are taking advantage of the (Maratha reservation) agitation and indulging in violence. Such violence will not be tolerated and video footages have been obtained of attempts being made to kill people by setting them on fire.

title: Why a pro-Palestine activist tossed live mice at a UK McDonald's
description: A pro-Palestine activist caused panic at a McDonald's in Birmingham by tossing live mice colored in the shades of the Palestinian flag. The incident was captured on video, showing two women reacting with shock and screaming. The activist shouted slogans supporting Palestine and boycotting Israel before driving away. McDonald's confirmed that the mice were removed, and the restaurant was sanitized. Pro-Palestine activists have been urging boycotts of brands supporting Israel, including McDonald's. These protests have coincided with clashes between law enforcement and demonstrators in London.

title: Skill development: Naidu walks out of Rajahmundry jail
description: The high court said that conditional bail is being granted only on medical grounds without going into the merits of the case. The high court said that Naidu can get treatment at a hospital of his choice, and he should surrender before the jail authorities after four weeks.

title: PM Modi attends Meri Maati Mera Desh campaign
'I always had the drive in me, but I lacked...': Kohli on his career
description: Star India batter Virat Kohli has acknowledged making several changes along his journey, particularly in terms of discipline and lifestyle. He admitted that while he always possessed the inner drive and passion, he recognised there was a lack of professionalism in his approach earlier. Kohli highlighted the transformation in his commitment and lifestyle choices, indicating a deliberate shift towards a more disciplined and professional regimen to enhance his performance and approach to the game.

title: What does the yellow star worn by Israel's UN envoy mean?
description: Israel's UN ambassador, Gilad Erdan, courted controversy by wearing a yellow star on his chest during a speech at the Security Council, pledging to wear it until the body condemns Hamas. The yellow star is a symbol of the persecution faced by Jews during the Holocaust. Erdan's action was criticized by Yad Vashem, Israel's Holocaust memorial, which urged him to wear the Israeli flag instead. The Security Council has been deadlocked and has not adopted any resolution on the Israel-Hamas conflict.

title: Mahua Moitra to appear before Ethics Committee on Nov 2
description: Trinamool Congress MP Mahua Moitra has agreed to appear before the Lok Sabha Ethics Committee on November 2 regarding the cash-for-query complaint filed against her by BJP MP Nishikant Dubey. Moitra also expressed her desire to cross-examine businessman Darshan Hiranandani, who accused her of taking bribes to target the Adani Group. Moitra questioned whether the Ethics Committee is the appropriate forum for examining allegations of criminality, emphasizing the need to involve law enforcement agencies.

title: 'Very proud feeling': Karan Kundra on his new house
description: Actor Karan Kundrra, known for hosting multiple reality shows, is set to host Temptation Island India. In an interview, Karan revealed that he prefers being impromptu and spontaneous rather than relying on scripts. Having hosted reality shows like Roadies, Love School, and Splitsvilla, he believes his understanding of human nature helps contestants open up to him. Karan also expressed pride in buying a new house in Mumbai, saying it was a personal achievement for his family.

title: WC: Who will Pandya replace once he returns fit?
description: Captain Rohit Sharma and the team management are undoubtedly pondering over the crucial decision of whom to substitute with star all-rounder Hardik Pandya once he returns from his injury for the upcoming World Cup matches. Pandya suffered an ankle injury after slipping in his follow-through during a match against Bangladesh. Former India allrounder and 1983 World Cup-winning hero Madan Lal feels captain Rohit will need Pandya to be fit in the upcoming matches, especially the knockouts.

title: ED grills arrested Bengal minister Jyoti Priya Mallick
description: Mallick, aged 66 and holding the position of state forest minister, was taken to the ED office at the CGO complex in Salt Lake on Monday night after being declared fit and discharged from the hospital. He had been receiving medical treatment following a collapse in court on October 27.

title: UK man uses Google Earth to find stolen car
description: A car owner in the United Kingdom managed to track down his £23,000 (INR 23.31 lakh) car after it was stolen from his Birmingham home, thanks to Google Earth.

title: Karwa Chauth: Best messages, quotes, wishes and images to share
description: Karwa Chauth is a festival in India that celebrates the bond between married couples. The festival involves fasting for the health and longevity of the husband, prayers for eternal love between the couple, and breaking the fast at the sight of the moon. It is celebrated primarily in Northern India and falls on the fourth day after the full moon in the month of Kartik. On this day, people exchange greetings and wishes, expressing their love and well wishes for married couples.

title: 'Argoland': Scientists finally discover 'lost continent'
Hacking alert row: Apple says attackers well-funded; BJP refutes snooping allegations
description: Several opposition leaders in India have claimed to have received an alert from Apple, warning them of state-sponsored attackers trying to compromise their iPhones. The Congress party has accused the government of being behind the snooping, which the ruling BJP has denied. Apple has responded by stating that the attackers are well-funded and their techniques are sophisticated. The company also said that it cannot provide information on the specific causes of these warnings. The BJP called the allegations baseless.

title: Poaching pilots: AI & Akasa Air CEOs exchange barbs
description: The CEOs of Air India and Akasa Air have engaged in a private exchange of barbs over pilot recruitment, with Akasa accusing its rival of rule violations, according to a Reuters report. The dispute arose when Akasa accused Air India of violating government policies regarding notice periods for pilots.

title: Opposition hacking claims: Apple issued advisory in 150 nations, I-T minister Ashwini Viashnaw says
Antisemitic comments surge across Chinese social media
description: Antisemitic comments have surged on Chinese social media platforms amid the recent conflict between Israel and Hamas. Chinese users have been searching for and mentioning the term "anti-Jew" on WeChat, while negative feedback has flooded the film "Schindler's List" on streaming site Bilibili and film critique platform Douban. Online hostility has also targeted influencers who identify as Jewish. The reasons behind this surge in antisemitic comments are unclear, but it may be influenced by China's pro-Palestinian stance during the conflict.

title: Halloween surprise: Nasa’s Juno spots eerie 'face' on Jupiter
description: Nasa's Juno spacecraft captured an image during a flyby of Jupiter that appears to show a spooky, stretched-out face. The photograph, taken on September 7, showcases a region in Jupiter's far northern area known as Jet N7. Nasa likened the image to a Cubist artwork, paying homage to Pablo Picasso, and released it just ahead of Halloween. Juno's images are publicly accessible, and Nasa encourages the public to assist in analyzing the vast data the spacecraft gathers.

title: Sniper attack? Senior cop shot dead in Manipur
description: A sub-divisional police officer was shot dead by suspected militants at Manipur's Moreh town, which is along the Indo-Myanmar border.

title: Banks to remain shut on these days in November
description: Bank holidays November 2023: Notably, digital banking services like UPI, Mobile Banking, and Internet Banking remain unaffected by bank holidays and can be accessed by customers at any time.

title: Suspected gunman takes hostages in Japan
description: A shooting incident occurred at a hospital in Toda, Japan, leaving two people injured. The suspect, believed to be aged between 50s and 70s, has taken hostages and is currently in a post office. The motive behind the shooting is unclear, and authorities are working to resolve the situation. Japan has strict gun-control regulations, with residents prohibited from owning or trading firearms. Japan is often praised for its safety, largely attributed to its strict gun-control regulations.

title: Everyone in oppn received Apple alerts: Rahul on hacking row
description: Showing a copy of the warning e-mail received by several opposition leaders from their phone manufacturer (Apple) about 'state-sponsored attackers trying to compromise their phone' in a press conference, Rahul Gandhi said, "Do as much phone tapping as you want, I don't care. You can take my phone, I am not scared". Hitting out at the Modi government, the former Congress president added, "As soon as Adani is touched, intelligence agencies, snooping are deployed".

title: Not scared, ready to surrender my phone: Rahul on hacking row
description: Showing a copy of the warning e-mail received by several opposition leaders from their phone manufacturer (Apple) about 'state-sponsored attackers trying to compromise their phone' in a press conference, Rahul Gandhi said, "Do as much phone tapping as you want, I don't care. You can take my phone, I am not scared". Hitting out at the Modi government, the former Congress president added, "As soon as Adani is touched, intelligence agencies, snooping are deployed".

title: Many ways to earn than get locked in BB house: Kiran Karmarkar
description: Kiran Karmarkar shares how he has never watched Bigg Boss and has not been offered any wildcard entry in the show. Kiran's ex-wife Rinku Karmarkar is currently in Bigg Boss 17.

title: Why Pakistan cricket team used Zomato to order food
description: The Pakistan cricket team chose to skip dinner at their team hotel ahead of their World Cup match against Bangladesh and instead ordered food through the app Zomato. They ordered biryani, kebabs, and chap from Kolkata's Zam Zam Restaurant. The restaurant initially had no idea the order was from the Pakistan team. Former captain Wasim Akram criticized the team's dietary habits, suggesting they eat too much meat. Pakistan's head coach, Grant Bradburn, blamed their poor performance on unfamiliar Indian conditions.

title: US' new nuclear bomb: 24 times stronger than Hiroshima
description: The Pentagon is planning to develop a new nuclear bomb, the B61-13, which will be 24 times more powerful than the one used in Hiroshima. This decision comes after China announced its intention to double its nuclear arsenal by 2030. The US Department of Defense stated that the new bomb will provide the President with more options to target larger and tougher military areas. The development of the B61-13 is part of the US's ongoing evaluation of the global security situation. This decision is based on an ongoing evaluation of the world's security situation.

title: '70-hour week': Harsh Goenka differs with Narayana Murthy
description: Harsh Goenka, RPG Enterprises Chairman has expressed a divergent viewpoint from Murthy. In a tweet on X (formerly Twitter), Goenka asserted his endorsement of a hybrid work model, declaring the "5-day office week is dead."

title: 'Indians can visit Thailand visa-free from Nov 10'
description: Thailand has waived visa requirements for Indian citizens, allowing them to visit the country visa-free from November 2023 to May 2024. This move is aimed at attracting more Indian tourists to Thailand. This comes shortly after Sri Lanka announced visa-free entry for visitors from seven countries, including India. Indian travelers are being actively targeted by tourism boards of various countries post-Covid. India has been Thailand's fourth largest source market for tourism this year.

title: Retired IAS officer slaps woman for taking dog inside lift
description: An argument broke out between a retired IAS officer and a woman over bringing a dog into a lift in Noida. The officer allegedly slapped the woman after she tried to take his phone. The incident was captured on CCTV and went viral on social media. Police are investigating the matter.

title: Andhra HC grants interim bail to TDP chief Chandrababu Naidu
description: Naidu was arrested by the Criminal Investigation Department (CID) on September 9 in connection with the multi-crore skill development scam case.

title: Have to make India a developed nation in next 25yrs, PM says
description: PM Modi on Tuesday said the way August 15 is a day of celebration of India's Independence and January 26 of our Republic, October 31 has become "a festival of communication of nationalism". He was addressing a 'Rashtriya Ekta Diwas' event at Statue of Unity in Gujarat. The next 25 years are the most crucial 25 years of this decade for India ... we have to make India prosperous, we have to make India developed .

title: Apple has finally killed the TouchBar in MacBook Pro
description: Apple has officially discontinued the Touch Bar in the MacBook Pro with M3 models. The Touch Bar, introduced in 2016, was a divisive feature that received mixed reviews. Some loved it, while others found it gimmicky and preferred physical function keys. The Touch Bar was criticized for being too sensitive and not compatible with all macOS applications. Apple has not given a specific reason for discontinuing it, but it is likely due to its lack of popularity. The Touch Bar was a thin OLED display that replaced function keys and allowed for various controls and shortcuts.

title: Govt trying to hack into my phone, email: TMC MP Mahua Moitra
description: Sharing screenshots of the warning from Apple, she wrote on X, "Received text and email from Apple warning me that the government is trying to hack into my phone and email. Home Minister's Office - get a life. Adani and PMO bullies - your fear makes me pity you. In her post, Mahua also mentioned that Shiv Sena MP Priyanka Chaturvedi and few other INDIA alliance leaders have received the warnings. The TMC leader is currently being probed by the Parliament Ethics Committee in the cash-for-query case.

title: 'ED to arrest Kejriwal when he appears before them on Nov 2'
description: Kejriwal has been issued summons to appear before the ED for questioning in a money laundering case linked to the alleged excise policy scam. The agency will record his statement once he deposes before the investigating officer of the case in Delhi.

title: Mamaearth IPO opens today: Should you subscribe?
description: Mamaearth IPO has garnered mixed opinions from analysts, primarily due to not-so-cheap valuations, despite pricing adjustments in the offering. The share price range falls between Rs 308-324, valuing the company at approximately Rs 10,500 crore at the upper end.

title: Tata Motors to get Rs 766 cr compensation: Here's why
description: Tata Motors announced on Monday that they have secured an arbitral award amounting to Rs 765.78 crore as compensation for their investment in the now defunct plant in Singur, West Bengal.

title: Nature’s heist: How floods destroy Rs 400-cr cash here
description: The Bank of Maharashtra's currency vault in Sitabuldi, Nagpur was flooded during the recent 9/23 floods, causing several hundred crores of rupees in paper currency to be damaged. It took over 24 hours to pump out the water from the bank premises. The bank's zonal manager did not confirm or deny the flooding of the vault, but video clips showed the floodwaters entering the currency chest. The RBI has dispatched an inspection team to replace the damaged notes and replenish the currency vault. The bank is also considering taking measures to prevent future flooding.

title: 'Murdered LA model was bound, gagged inside fridge'
description: New details have emerged regarding the tragic death of Los Angeles model Maleesa Mooney. Authorities disclosed that Mooney, 31, was found dead inside her refrigerator in her apartment in September. The recent autopsy report has now revealed that Mooney had been severely beaten, bound, and gagged before being placed inside her refrigerator. The report also mentioned clothing items wrapped around her face and neck, and a gag made of clothing was found in her mouth.

title: 'Dravid has no ego': Shoaib Malik shares a personal anecdote
description: Following his illustrious career as one of cricket's finest batters, Rahul Dravid made a seamless transition from his role as the head of the National Cricket Academy to coaching India's under-19, India 'A' and ultimately the senior Indian team. Shoaib Malik, the former Pakistan captain, lauded Dravid, recounting a personal anecdote that underscores the current India coach's meticulous and industrious approach, which is undeniably propelling Indian cricket to greater heights and has taken it within sight of another ODI World Cup title on home soil.

title: Is this how Israel plans to change civilian reality in Gaza Strip?
description: While Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's office has downplayed the report, describing it as a "concept paper" and a hypothetical exercise, the proposal has reignited concerns in Egypt about Israel's intentions towards Gaza and evoked painful memories for Palestinians of their displacement during Israel's creation in 1948. The most favored option suggests relocating Gaza's civilian population to tent cities in northern Sinai, followed by the construction of permanent cities and a humanitarian corridor.

title: ‘Vindicated’, ED set to pile up pressure in Delhi's liquor policy case
description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) plans to gather more evidence against Manish Sisodia and other Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) leaders during their trial, following the Supreme Court's denial of bail to Sisodia. The ED aims to establish that the amount of money lost to the exchequer due to changes in Delhi's liquor policy by the AAP government was higher than initially estimated. The agency has already attached properties worth over Rs 128 crore belonging to alleged beneficiaries, including Sisodia, and the SC's decision strengthens the ED's probe against the AAP leadership.

title: Movie actor Renjusha found dead in Kerala apartment
Kerala 'bomber' took a room, did FB Live & surrendered
description: The accused in the Jehovah's Witnesses convention explosion, Dominic Martin, briefly stayed in a lodge in Thrissur before surrendering to the police. He confessed his crime on Facebook Live from the room he stayed in. Martin checked-in using his original Aadhaar card, paid with UPI, and only stayed for 10 minutes before leaving. The police decided not to immediately arrest him to verify his account and investigate if he received assistance. The NIA team also questioned the accused, and a case has been booked under relevant sections of the law.

title: Aligarh Muslim Univ to launch its own satellite
description: The Indian National Space Promotion and Authorisation Centre (IN-SPACe) has approved Aligarh Muslim University's proposal for their first satellite, named after their founder. The satellite, a 3U CubeSat, aims to study economic growth in India's poorest districts, implement image compression technology, and test various in-house built sub-systems. The project is expected to be launched in six months. This approval comes after Anna University became the first Indian university to launch a student-made satellite in 2009.

title: Israel-Hamas war: Netanyahu's ‘Mr Security’ image fades as rivals want him out
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is facing increasing calls to resign following the recent violence between Israel and Hamas. Many critics argue that Netanyahu failed to protect Israeli citizens and ignored Hamas' true intentions. Former defense minister Moshe Yaalon accused Netanyahu of engaging in political maneuvering and questioned his ability to lead the military campaign. Netanyahu's popularity has plummeted in polls, while opposition leader Benny Gantz's popularity has soared.

title: Apple cuts the starting price of the new 14-inch MacBook Pro model
description: Apple has slashed the price of its 14-inch MacBook Pro in India by Rs 30,000, making it a more attractive option for buyers. The new M3 MacBook Pro now starts at Rs 1,69,900, down from the initial launch price of Rs 1,99,900 for the M2 version. This move is unusual for Apple, as it typically discounts older models rather than newly released ones. The price cut aims to make the MacBook Pro more competitive in the Indian market and increase sales in the country.

title: World Cup: How Indian bowlers have hunted down opposition batters
description: Indian bowlers, including Mohammed Shami and Jasprit Bumrah, showcased their control and consistency in troubling the best batting line-ups. In a dominating win against England, the bowlers stole the spotlight with their impressive performances. Bumrah opened the floodgates by getting early wickets, while Shami unleashed his skills to dismiss Ben Stokes. Local boy Kuldeep also contributed by taking important wickets. With their strong bowling attack, India now has a claim to having the most glamorous bowling attack in the World Cup.

title: 'Just killed him on God's command': Man walks into police stn
Rapper Badshah quizzed over promoting betting app
description: Rapper Badshah has been questioned by the Maharashtra cyber police for promoting the betting app FairPlay, which illegally streamed IPL matches, causing a loss of Rs 100 crore to media company Viacom18. Badshah's lawyer clarified that he was questioned as a witness and not as an accused. Other celebrities, including actor Sanjay Dutt, may also be called for further statements. FairPlay is being investigated by the Enforcement Directorate for money-laundering. Viacom18 has filed a complaint against the app for copyright infringement.

title: Messi wins 8th Ballon d'Or as Bonmati claims women's award
description: For Messi, this prestigious trophy primarily celebrates his awe-inspiring performances at the previous year's World Cup held in Qatar. During the tournament, he single-handedly propelled Argentina to victory, netting seven goals and earning the title of the tournament's standout player. Bonmati also played a pivotal role in Spain's triumph at the World Cup held in Australia in August. The 25-year-old midfielder earned the distinction of being named the World Cup's best player as the Spanish team surmounted various off-field challenges.

title: BTech student's death: What snatchers took away
description: A first-year BTech student, Kirti Singh, was targeted by snatchers while returning home from college in an auto. She fell from the auto and sustained critical injuries, ultimately passing away at a private hospital. Kirti was a dedicated student focused on her studies and had dreams of becoming an engineer and traveling abroad. Her family and friends remember her as a courageous and determined girl. Her father called for increased security for women on the roads, and one of the snatchers was killed in an encounter.

title: ‘Parts of tigers, rhinos being used in Chinese meds’
description: A probe by the Environmental Investigation Agency (EIA) has found that body parts of leopards and pangolins, which are highly trafficked and endangered mammals, are used in at least 88 traditional Chinese medicines. The medicines, manufactured by 72 Chinese firms and licensed by the National Medical Products Administration (NMPA), also contain tiger and rhino parts, in violation of the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES). The report also identifies 62 banks and financial institutions that have invested in Chinese pharmaceutical groups manufacturing these products.

title: 'Good-looking' girls being paid to file fake rape cases: Goa DIG
description: Goa police have uncovered a large-scale racket where attractive young women from poor families are being bribed to file false rape cases across India. The investigation began when two women from Gujarat were found to be extorting money from clients by threatening them with fake rape cases. The women would contact clients online, travel with them to Goa, and then demand large sums of money, threatening to file rape cases if they didn't comply. So far, two rape cases have been registered in Goa and one in Gujarat.

title: 11-yr-old girl identifies burglar from 110 photos
description: An 11-year-old girl in Mumbai helped the police arrest a burglar who had been evading capture for over a year. The girl identified the suspect from a collection of 110 photographs and a video shown to her by the police. The burglar had stolen gold jewelry worth Rs 2.4 lakh from the girl's residence. The accused, Nikhil alias Deepak Vaishya, was arrested at Andheri railway station and found to be in possession of stolen jewelry worth Rs 22.6 lakh. He had been involved in at least 13 cases of house break-ins and thefts.

title: UP: 4 kids dead as 2 school vehicles collide head on
description: Five people, including four students aged between six and 11, were killed in a collision between a school bus and a school van in Uttar Pradesh's Budaun district. Thirteen children were injured and admitted to the hospital. The condition of three children is critical. The incident has led to an investigation into the cause of the accident and the arrest of the bus driver. This is the third such accident involving school vehicles in the region within a week.

title: Ratan Tata clears this fake news related to Afghanistan-Pak match
description: Ratan Tata, Chairman Emeritus of Tata Sons and Chairman of Tata Trusts, returned to Twitter after a four-month hiatus to address fake news surrounding his patronage of Afghan cricket player Rashid Khan. Tata clarified that he had not made any announcements or offered rewards to any players, and urged his followers to verify messages before believing them. Social media has been flooded with fraudulent claims that Tata had announced a reward for Khan after Afghanistan's victory over Pakistan in the Cricket World Cup. Afghanistan has also secured victories over Sri Lanka and England in the tournament.

title: How Hardik Pandya twist corrected India’s selection glitch
description: The injury to Hardik Pandya has forced the Indian cricket team to reevaluate their playing XI and make necessary changes. The inclusion of Shardul Thakur over Mohammad Shami was seen as a mistake, but Pandya's absence allowed the team management to rectify it.

title: Apple launches new MacBook Pro models with M3 processors
description: Apple has unveiled its latest MacBook Pro lineup, featuring a range of new chips including the M3, M3 Pro, and M3 Max. These chips promise improved CPU and GPU performance, with advanced capabilities such as Dynamic Caching and ray tracing. The MacBook Pro models also come with a Liquid Retina XDR display, built-in 1080p camera, six-speaker sound system, and various connectivity options. The M3 Pro and M3 Max chips offer faster speeds than their predecessors, with the M3 Max supporting up to 128 GB of RAM. The laptops also boast a 22-hour battery life and a new Space Black color option.

title: Matthew Perry moved house 3 weeks ago; signed new movie
description: Fans of actor Matthew Perry were shocked by his untimely death, which was reportedly due to accidental drowning in his jacuzzi. Before this tragedy, Perry was said to be in a happy state of mind, having recently moved into a new house and signed on for a new Hollywood movie. The Friends star was also working on other projects and script ideas before his passing at the age of 54.
